description: Borrowed from Latin vegetatum, past participle of vegeto (“I enliven, I arouse”).

verbs.description: vegetate (third-person singular simple present vegetates, present participle vegetating, simple past and past participle vegetated)

entries.meaning: (of a plant) To grow or sprout.
(of a wart etc) To spread abnormally.
(informal) To live or spend a period of time in a dull, inactive, unchallenging way.
